						<summary>

						<p>On the door-post of the entrance into the Mallēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II, 1400 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1322, Vikrama, Māgha śu. 10, Monday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1401 A.D., January 24, f.d.t. °28.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift of land by purchase to the god Doḍḍamalnātha of Kuṇundōṟu by Chēmakurti Annama-nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
